    "title": "Libboost Dependency Pathing Issues with Ubuntu 20.04LTS",
    "body": "Ubuntu 20.04LTS\r\n\r\nI already resolved this on my system, but want to share to prevent headaches in other devs.\r\n\r\n`configure: error: Could not find a version of the boost_program_options library!`\r\n\r\nFollowing the instructions in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/build-unix.md got me stuck on this error. I resolved it by running `sudo apt-get autoremove libboost1.71-dev:amd64`, `sudo apt-get install libboost-all-dev` and then running configure with `./configure --disable-wallet --with-gui=no --with-boost-libdir=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu`\r\n\r\nI couldn't get it to work with different installations of libboost or with any of the other flags for configure.",
